# Proxy admin-support API calls to the Heroku backend so the admin session
# cookie is first-party (Safari/iOS block third-party cookies — direct
# cross-origin calls break the support login on mobile). Scoped to the one
# path prefix the admin app uses; a blanket /api/* would put the whole
# backend same-origin with the marketing pages and their cookie. The 200!
# forces the rewrite even if a static file ever shadows the path.
# Backend host also appears in src/setupProxy.js and netlify/edge-functions/invite.ts.
/api/admin/support/*  https://keeep-9dde9ef1f49f.herokuapp.com/api/admin/support/:splat  200!

/invite        /inviteLink.html    200
/invitelink    /inviteLink.html    200
/inviteLink    /inviteLink.html    200
/*             /index.html         200
